<section id="fs-idm359085856" class="questions">
<exercise id="fs-idm352552432">
<problem id="fs-idm360219088">
<para id="fs-idm628963632"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68066"/>What is the process for developing a budgeted balance sheet?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm346460048">
<para id="fs-idm342944336">The budgeted income statement includes the estimated revenue and expenses for the company. Using historical data on cash collections helps plan when the cash will be received and is used to develop the cash collections schedule. The company applies its payment policies on its purchases and other items requiring cash expenditures. This creates the cash payments schedule. Information from the cash collections schedule, cash payments schedule, and the capital expense budget are combined to develop the cash budget. The information from the cash budget and the ending balance sheet from the preceding year are used to develop the budgeted balance sheet.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
